      "content": "i'm just really frustrated because i've been tossing and turning for hours and i feel like i'm going to be a wreck tomorrow. if i just have one single sip or a tiny amount, like a teaspoon, is that really going to make a difference in terms of safety? it seems like such a small amount that it shouldn't be a big deal if it helps me actually get some rest.",
